# CASM's lexer accepts unshifted ($41-$5A) or shifted ($C1-$DA) PETSCII as
# identifier bytes; the two labels above are the SAME letters ("LOOP") in
# the two different registers, which the symbol table must treat as two
# genuinely distinct, independently-resolving names -- proving case-sensitive
# identity through real Pass 1/Pass 2, not just symbols.s's own isolated
# symcase1 fixture (WP27).
